review_blob: Citrus and cherry nose. Mild acidity, followed by slightly bready funk. Pleasant but not overly complex.
Light tart citrus and ripe pineapple in nose. Orange and clove dominate taste. Light tartness evaporates off the palate. Bright mouthfeel.
beer_name: Trinity Magical Brettanomyces Tour #6, Farmhouse Brett

review_blob: Nose is pineapple and bread. Taste mildly tart saison. Finishes unpleasantly with a blood-like thing.
beer_name: Trinity Magical Brettanomyces Tour #5, Brett Naardenensis

review_blob: Nose dominated by lemon with a touch of funk. Tastealso lemon, with hay, oak, and a touch of honey.

Nice nose farmhouse nose with lime. Taste is pretty straightforward to style. Dry hopping privided a nice bright character to the beer. Preferred to keep the yeast out as it muddied up the whole dry hop thing.
Lots of barnyard and funk in nose. Funk and similar to #1 in taste but not as dry. Had dide by side with #1
beer_name: Trinity Magical Brettanomyces Tour #3, Brett Bouckaertii

review_blob: A lot of classic brett character-barnyard in nose and taste. Very dry and very tart. Similar to #3 but drier.
beer_name: Trinity Magical Brettanomyces Tour #1, Brett drie

review_blob: Funky nose. Really fruity with a hint of pear. Sweeter than some of the others in the series.
beer_name: Trinity Magical Brettanomyces Tour #7, Brett Anomala

review_blob: Initially thought this beer was dominated by pepper but pairing it with some siracha pulled pork numbed my palate to the spicyness and allowed the chocolate and cinnamon to cone through better. Much better with food than as a sipper.
Poured from 22 oz bottle. Pinkish head dissipared quickly. Light cherry aroma. Tasted malt and sweet cherry. Like the canned pie filling.

I got this in a previously used & cleaned growler but this tastes sour to me. Hope my growler was to blame because this is the first beer from Iron Bird that hasnt awesome and there are more than enough crappy breweries already.
Dank aroma. Should I drink it or smoke it? Bitterness well in balance. Hop flavor! Touch of tropical and peach. Best IPA Ive had in a while.
Nice brown kind of pushing into porterish territorry but delicious at any rate. Notes of coffee and chocolate kind of overwhelmed hop flavor.

Poured from a 22oz bottle at CCs last homestand of a disastrous season. Not much from the aroma. Punchy malt character kind of like a Laughing Lab on steroids. Caramel, chocolate and a touch of roast. A nice rich beer to drown my sorrows in.
Strawberry jam nose. Taste is jam on toast with a little extra bready sweetness. Light acidity leads to lingering fresh strawberry.
Nose is bourbon barrel with a touch of brett. Taste is also bourbon, with oak and a healthy dose of sour. Finishes super clean.
Tart wine nose. Dry cherry and red wine nose. Well balanced acidity. Very well done.
Great dry hop nose (falconers flight Im told). Nice lemony finish very well balanced. I could drink a lot of this.
Bourbon nose. Taste is bourbon, oak. Not much acidity to distinguish it from other bourbon beers, but certainly not offensive.
beer_name: Paradox Beer In the Spirit of Skully No. 2

review_blob: Nice apple pie nose, a little tart. Taste is of cinnamon and apple underneath tartness that dominates.
Wine, cherry nose. Clean acidity punctuated by tart cherry. Spritzy carbonation helps the beer vanish off the palate.
Nice tart fruity nose. Lemon, fruity taste, nice carbonation. No enteric. Clean acid finsh. Way better than 7 Day.
Nose dominated by enteric acid (baby diaper) yuck. Taste was much better but enteric still there. Lets hope the barrel aged version is better. Woody

Like old friends you dont visit often enough, then wonder why you dont when youre having a great time with them. Rich caramel with classic cascade in both aroma and taste. Superbly balanced classic apa.
Light coffe and roast aroma. Mild roasty bitterness, coffee and bakers chocolate. Thin body.

2014 bomber. This beer comes at you in waves. Tart, cherry nose with malt in the background. Seriously sour as the bottle says. Cherry tart gives way to wheat bread sweetness, which in turn fades quietly into dry acidity.
Served on cask at the brewery. Huge head over thetop of the glass. Light coffee aroma. Taste of malt, bakers chocolate. Clean dry finish with lingering roasty but soft bitterness.
Served on cask at the brewery. Nice rich caramel taste with a clean malty finish. One of the best small brewries in Co Springs.

Lovely noble hop aroma, pours bright golden. Bready malt followed by sharp noble hops. Lively carbonation. Very nice to this point but a hint of vegetal at the end. Would be an awesome beer without that.
beer_name: Full Sail Session Export Golden Lager

review_blob: Tart, fruity nose. Earthy, almost leathery finish. Dry finsh that disappeared nicely.
Sweet, with caramel and white wine. Seems like it would benefit from cellar time. Would buy again.
beer_name: River North J Marie - Chardonnay Barrel
